author: stefan2
msg: On the fsfs-format7 branch:  speed up directory cache access by changing
addressing from fs_id to the rev,item keys used for most data.  This
further reduces the DAG access / traversal overhead.
Unfortunately, this will only work for committed data, i.e. when rev>=0.
We are stuck with the fs_id-based cache for txn data.
(parse_dir_entries): unparse fs_id only in case of an error
(locate_dir_cache): construct the required key as well
